right before I fall asleep.

00:30:45.390 --> 00:30:47.450
So in the past I've
used some apps--

00:30:47.450 --> 00:30:49.670
sleep cycle apps--
you give it a window

00:30:49.670 --> 00:30:52.150
and it tries to wake you up
when you're in lighter sleep.

00:30:52.150 --> 00:30:54.070
Did you study any
of that, or have you

00:30:54.070 --> 00:30:57.140
tried any of that
for waking up easier?

00:30:57.140 --> 00:30:59.060
ARIANNA HUFFINGTON:
You mean to wake up

00:30:59.060 --> 00:31:01.254
when you need to wake
up to start your day?

00:31:01.254 --> 00:31:02.170
Is that what you mean?

00:31:02.170 --> 00:31:02.440
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:31:02.440 --> 00:31:03.700
Well it works for naps too.

00:31:03.700 --> 00:31:04.640
But longer--

00:31:04.640 --> 00:31:05.770
ARIANNA HUFFINGTON: Yeah.

00:31:05.770 --> 00:31:11.220
Well actually what
I recommend is

00:31:11.220 --> 00:31:17.530
that you get enough sleep so
that you don't need an alarm.

00:31:17.530 --> 00:31:21.960
And really the science
shows that you can overeat,

00:31:21.960 --> 00:31:24.400
but you cannot oversleep.

00:31:24.400 --> 00:31:30.410
So whatever the time is that
your body and your mind needs

00:31:30.410 --> 00:31:32.060
is the time to give yourself.

00:31:32.060 --> 00:31:34.790
I mean, you know, it's not
going to happen every day.

00:31:34.790 --> 00:31:37.460
I mean even with all the
evangelizing I'm doing,

00:31:37.460 --> 00:31:42.060
I only get it done
about 90% of the time.

00:31:42.060 --> 00:31:44.160
And it doesn't matter
where you start.

00:31:44.160 --> 00:31:47.410
Maybe you'll get it
done 50% of the time.

00:31:47.410 --> 00:31:49.105
There is no wrong
place to start.

00:31:52.330 --> 00:31:55.830
The important thing is that
where you want to end up in

00:31:55.830 --> 00:31:58.380
is to be able to
wake up refreshed.

00:32:02.380 --> 00:32:04.380
And it's not really
as hard as you think,

00:32:04.380 --> 00:32:08.200
because you are so much more
productive doing your day,

00:32:08.200 --> 00:32:11.510
that you find that it
becomes easier and easier

00:32:11.510 --> 00:32:14.320
to actually give
yourself that time.

00:32:14.320 --> 00:32:18.350
And you also learn
what to say no to.

00:32:18.350 --> 00:32:20.880
And in fact,
especially for women.

00:32:20.880 --> 00:32:23.950
I just want to remind you all
that no is a complete sentence.

00:32:27.950 --> 00:32:30.270
And that again
helps you prioritize

00:32:30.270 --> 00:32:32.930
what makes us more effective,
productive, and happier.

