00:33:57.990 --> 00:33:59.860
But they look great
on your nightstand.

00:33:59.860 --> 00:34:03.220
So anyway, if you wanted another
way to make sure you wake up,

00:34:03.220 --> 00:34:05.020
take a look at that.

00:34:05.020 --> 00:34:07.260
Or you can put your
phone in another room

00:34:07.260 --> 00:34:10.020
where you can still hear it.

00:34:10.020 --> 00:34:12.600
In terms of wisdom, yes.

00:34:12.600 --> 00:34:17.330
I feel that first of
all, if we recognize

00:34:17.330 --> 00:34:22.560
that we have a place of wisdom
in us, every major religion

00:34:22.560 --> 00:34:25.929
and many scientists have
talked about that place.

00:34:25.929 --> 00:34:29.190
I mean, Archimedes, the
Greek mathematician, said,

00:34:29.190 --> 00:34:32.480
"Give me a place to stand,
and I can move the world."

00:34:32.480 --> 00:34:35.198
And so we all have that place.

00:34:35.198 --> 00:34:37.239
It's just that most of
the time we are completely

00:34:37.239 --> 00:34:39.330
disconnected from it.

00:34:39.330 --> 00:34:42.550
So the first thing is that
we have our own inner wisdom.

00:34:42.550 --> 00:34:43.929
And we all are aware of it.

00:34:43.929 --> 00:34:50.070
When we pay attention,
how much wiser

00:34:50.070 --> 00:34:52.460
we will become about
people, about what we should

00:34:52.460 --> 00:34:55.580
be doing next, then
when we're just

00:34:55.580 --> 00:35:00.070
rushing through and reacting
to what is happening.

00:35:00.070 --> 00:35:04.300
But also, I do
love reading books

00:35:04.300 --> 00:35:07.810
of spirituality,
philosophy, poetry.

00:35:07.810 --> 00:35:11.510
In fact, these are the
only books I read at night.

00:35:11.510 --> 00:35:13.810
And I read books at night.

00:35:13.810 --> 00:35:15.180
I really like books.

00:35:15.180 --> 00:35:18.670
I like learning them,
and underlining them,

00:35:18.670 --> 00:35:21.220
and I like the
physicality of it.

00:35:21.220 --> 00:35:25.090
And also I like not bringing
screens to bed with me.

00:35:25.090 --> 00:35:27.790
So basically my bedroom
is a device-free zone.

00:35:30.640 --> 00:35:33.600
And also conversations
with people, absolutely.

00:35:33.600 --> 00:35:40.140
I particularly love talking to
scientists because for me it's

00:35:40.140 --> 00:35:43.680
just really exciting that we
are living at this intersection

00:35:43.680 --> 00:35:47.700
where modern science is
validating ancient wisdom.

00:35:47.700 --> 00:35:49.440
Like somebody-- I
highly recommend

00:35:49.440 --> 00:35:51.780
his work-- is Richard
Davidson, a professor

00:35:51.780 --> 00:35:55.540
