children, and they

00:37:36.700 --> 00:37:39.270
start texting across the table.

00:37:39.270 --> 00:37:41.800
And that is a lot
of consequences

00:37:41.800 --> 00:37:45.030
in how their brain develops,
how empathy develops,

00:37:45.030 --> 00:37:47.740
so that's really important.

00:37:47.740 --> 00:37:49.600
What has happened
with my own daughters

00:37:49.600 --> 00:37:53.240
is that they have become real
kind of for believers now.

00:37:53.240 --> 00:37:57.250
And we are each other's
set of support buddies when

00:37:57.250 --> 00:38:00.030
it comes to
sleeping, meditating,

00:38:00.030 --> 00:38:02.290
taking time for renewal.

00:38:02.290 --> 00:38:05.350
And it's really
fascinating to see

00:38:05.350 --> 00:38:08.330
how-- if anybody here has
been through AA, you know,

00:38:08.330 --> 00:38:12.720
you have your sponsors-- so we
are like each other's sponsors.

00:38:12.720 --> 00:38:18.180
Like the other day, my
daughter was kind of

00:38:18.180 --> 00:38:23.240
tempted to binge-watch
House of Cards.

00:38:23.240 --> 00:38:25.340
So she called me up,
and I talked her down.

00:38:30.810 --> 00:38:34.650
It's actually good to find-- we
call them also thrive buddies.

00:38:34.650 --> 00:38:36.860
It's good to find
a thrive buddy,

00:38:36.860 --> 00:38:39.150
when you decide to
make any change.

00:38:39.150 --> 00:38:43.450
And I recommend starting with
small, microscopic changes,

00:38:43.450 --> 00:38:46.160
whatever you choose
of the twelve steps.

00:38:46.160 --> 00:38:50.200
