00:50:15.492 --> 00:50:17.700
you have that doesn't
necessarily do with technology.

00:50:17.700 --> 00:50:20.390
Something that might resonate
with someone who again, may not

00:50:20.390 --> 00:50:22.780
have access to
internet or smartphone.

00:50:22.780 --> 00:50:24.780
ARIANNA HUFFINGTON: Who
may not have access to--

00:50:24.780 --> 00:50:25.700
AUDIENCE: Internet
or smartphone,

00:50:25.700 --> 00:50:27.990
or other forms of technology
that sort of speaks

00:50:27.990 --> 00:50:29.740
to a lot of the advice
that you're giving.

00:50:29.740 --> 00:50:30.440
ARIANNA HUFFINGTON: Absolutely.

00:50:30.440 --> 00:50:31.490
So you're right.

00:50:31.490 --> 00:50:36.920
I mean, technology is just
one aspect of our modern lives

00:50:36.920 --> 00:50:40.700
that makes it harder to
connect with ourselves.

00:50:40.700 --> 00:50:45.290
But we can have absolutely
no technology and still not

00:50:45.290 --> 00:50:46.330
connect with ourselves.

00:50:46.330 --> 00:50:49.930
We can find out other
avoidance measures.

00:50:49.930 --> 00:50:56.630
And that's why I think leaving
aside technology, prioritizing

00:50:56.630 --> 00:51:00.240
sort of time when we
can have stillness

00:51:00.240 --> 00:51:03.250
and silence in our lives,
even if it is five or 10

00:51:03.250 --> 00:51:05.420
minutes that we
want to start with,

00:51:05.420 --> 00:51:08.510
helps us connect with
that part of ourselves

00:51:08.510 --> 00:51:11.490
that so often we are
disconnected from.

00:51:11.490 --> 00:51:14.410
And if you think
of human evolution,

00:51:14.410 --> 00:51:17.490
we continue to evolve in
terms of our consciousness,

00:51:17.490 --> 00:51:20.420
in terms of our thoughts,
in terms of our feelings.

00:51:20.420 --> 00:51:26.200
And when we allow ourselves to
have that space in our lives,

00:51:26.200 --> 00:51:29.130
it just dramatically
affects how we

00:51:29.130 --> 00:51:32.070
respond to everything
that happens to us.

00:51:32.070 --> 00:51:35.100
And that's the same
in every culture.

00:51:35.100 --> 00:51:37.825
In Japanese culture-- we just
launched the Huffington Post

00:51:37.825 --> 00:51:41.000
in Japan-- and
the concept of ma,

00:51:41.000 --> 00:51:43.920
which literally
means pause, is just

00:51:43.920 --> 00:51:45.600
an essential part
of the culture.

00:51:45.600 --> 00:51:48.510
That's why you have
the tea ceremony, which

00:51:48.510 --> 00:51:52.950
is a time where you pause from
whatever it is you're doing,

00:51:52.950 --> 00:51:58.827
and just really allow that
sacred space in your day.

00:51:58.827 --> 00:51:59.660
